cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.CG, cs.DM, cs.SI. 

The paper deals with algorithms for computing the sparse Walsh-Hadamard transform of a vector, which is a problem in signal processing and information theory. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses tools from computational geometry (cs.CG) and data structures (cs.DS) to design the algorithm. Additionally, the paper mentions compressed sensing (cs.DM) and lossless condensers (cs.SI) as important technical tools used in the algorithm.
